# Enhanced Automatic Number Plate Recognition (ANPR) 

A real-time ANPR system built with Python, OpenCV, dlib, and pytesseract.  
Detects vehicles, reads license plates, and estimates vehicle speed.  

Patent Published: **Patent No: 202441025024 (IPO Journal 14/2024)**

---

## Features 

- Real-time vehicle detection and tracking  
- Automatic number plate recognition (OCR)  
- Speed estimation in km/h  
- Snapshots of vehicles exceeding speed limits saved automatically  
- Works with both video files and webcam  

---

## Technology Stack 

- **Python 3.10+**  
- **OpenCV** – Image & video processing  
- **dlib** – Correlation tracker for vehicle tracking  
- **pytesseract** – OCR for reading number plates  
- **NumPy** – Numerical operations  
- **Haar Cascades** – Pre-trained models for vehicle & plate detection  

---

## Folder Structure 
Enhanced-ANPR/
-src/
